<para><computeroutput>int CPostpone::moveEvent (std::istream &amp; m_In, std::ostream &amp; m_Out, <link linkend="_classCCalendar">CCalendar</link> &amp; cCalendar)</computeroutput></para>
<para>This method move event forward or back to a date or for some days/weeks/months/years which user writes. Could postpone event using munites, hours, days, months, years or even to a first working day(Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri) Could postpone forward or back to time.</para>

